FBIS4-27409 "dreas106bb_94002" FBIS-EAS-94-106 Daily Report 1 Jun 1994 INTER-ASIA AFFAIRS Further on Meeting on East Timor Held in Manila Further on Meeting on East Timor Held in Manila Visas of 10 Foreigners Cancelled BK0106124594 Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network in Tagalog 0500 GMT 1 Jun 94 BK0106124594 Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network Tagalog BFN [Text] The Bureau of Immigration and Deportation [BID] today cancelled the visas of 10 foreign nationals currently attending the Asia-Pacific Conference on East Timor [APCET]. Immigration Associate Commissioner Manuel Roxas reiterated that their action is in compliance with the government's position to bar foreigners attending the conference. Those foreigners who are now attending the APCET are believed to have gained entry into the country before their ban took effect. In this connection, immigration agents headed by Tom Natividad this morning served summons on 10 foreigners attending the conference at the Malcolm Hall of the University of the Philippines. Natividad said the foreigners should personally go to the immigration office before 0800. He clarified that they went to Malcolm Hall just to serve the subpoenas to the foreigners and not to arrest them. [Begin recording, in English] [Natividad] As I have said, we are just instructed to serve these to the secretariat, and that's all. [Unidentified correspondent] Sir, if they do not appear, what will happen? [Natividad] I don't know. [Unidentified correspondent] Sir, what's your name again? [Natividad] Tom Natividad. Intelligence Officer Tom Natividad. [Indistinct question from unidentified correspondent] [Natividad] No, it's not. (?It's) a subpoena that they have to appear at 0800 today. [end recording]
